  "summary": "Malicious code in core-dotenv (npm)",
  "details": "Core-dotenv@1.4.1 is a combosquat of the dotenv ecosystem. When required, it fetches a payload from hxxps://realase-0626[.]vercel[.]app/api/v1 and executes the response as arbitrary JavaScript code via Node.js vm.runInContext(), giving the remote server full control over the host. The C2 URL is obfuscated in the source as a hex-encoded character array.",
